On Thursday, June 16, 2005, at 04:36PM, Charles Durrrant <charliedurrant(-at-)gmail.com> wrote:

>OK...the pointing to #1 TDC bit.......this means when the rotor is
>pointing to the brass conducter in the distributer cap that goes to #1
>plug lead...........obvious when I thought about it........Hope I am
>not wrong in this assumption....?!?

This is what the mark on the body of the distributor is for. When the notch on the pulley points to zero on the timing scale the rotor will point to the mark on the distributor:

http://www.benplace.com/tdc/100_0283b.jpg

The pulley points to zero twice TDC #1 and #3 so keep rotating the engine until you line up both correctly.

